This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image processing and super resolution using deep learning techniques. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it involves the use of deep learning algorithms. Additionally, the paper may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories as it involves the use of convolutional neural networks for image processing and analysis.
